# Reflection Activity

### 1. Why can't a model learn in just one attempt?

A model cannot learn everything in one attempt because its first prediction is usually not correct. It needs multiple tries to understand the pattern in the data and improve its predictions.

### 2. Why is reducing error important?

Reducing error is important because lower error means better predictions. A model with less error is more reliable and performs better on new data.

### 3. What could happen if we adjust the model too aggressively?

If we adjust the model too aggressively, it may skip the best solution and make learning unstable. Instead of improving, the model may start making larger mistakes.

### 4. Why do we repeat the learning process multiple times?

The learning process is repeated multiple times so that the model can gradually reduce its errors and improve its performance. Each repetition helps the model learn a little better than before.
